public class HelloWorld {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
  System.out.println("Hello World");
 }
}

Step 1: Save file as HelloWorld.java
Step 2: Compile using javac
Step 3: Run using java command

This is the entry point of Java programs.

Conditional statements control program flow.

if-else Example:
if(age > 18) {
 System.out.println("Adult");
}

switch Example:
switch(day) {
 case 1: break;
}

Used for decision-making logic.

Loops repeat code execution.

Types:
- for loop
- while loop
- do-while loop

Example:
for(int i=0;i<5;i++) {
 System.out.println(i);
}

Used for iteration tasks.

Class is a blueprint.
Object is instance.

Example:
class Student {
 int id;
}

Student s = new Student();

Used to structure programs.
